sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT operator_id) 
FROM network_performance 
WHERE speed >= 5000;

external_knowledge:
- 'Peak hours' refers to periods of the day when network usage is typically at its highest; 
- 'Above-average' implies higher than the mean average calculated from all measurements; 
- 'Average speed' and 'average signal strength' are calculated for each performance ID and then compared to the overall average across all IDs.
- Network performance is typically measured in real-world scenarios to optimize network settings for better user experience.
